    correctOrder:[1,3,0,4,2],
    exp:'<strong>The correct sequence:</strong><br>1. Drought destroys harvest (initial cause).<br>2. Supply curve shifts leftwards (the diagrammatic representation).<br>3. At the original price, excess demand emerges (a shortage).<br>4. Price rises - choking off some demand and pulling out remaining supply (movements along the curves).<br>5. New equilibrium reached at higher price, lower quantity (final consequence).<br><br>This is a classic Edexcel analytical chain: <em>shock &rarr; curve shift &rarr; disequilibrium &rarr; price adjustment &rarr; new equilibrium</em>. Examiners reward chains that make each link explicit. Skipping straight from "drought" to "higher prices" misses the analysis marks - you must walk through the supply shift, the resulting shortage, and the price adjustment mechanism.'
