    correct:[0,1,3,4,5,6],
    exp:'<strong>Correct: A, B, D, E, F, G.</strong> Employees want higher wages (a cost); consumers want lower prices (lower TR); the community wants environmental standards (a cost); government may want firms to invest rather than distribute profit; suppliers want high input prices (a cost to the firm); short-run shareholders vs long-run investors is a genuine intra-shareholder conflict.<br><br>C is the trap: shareholders seeking maximum dividends is broadly <em>consistent</em> with profit maximisation &mdash; it is not a conflict. The real tension is between shareholder types (short-termists vs long-term investors) or between shareholders and other stakeholders, not between shareholders and profit maximisation per se.'
