    exp:'<strong>large &middot; small &middot; concentrated &middot; natural &middot; small &middot; competitive &middot; raises.</strong><br><br>This is the essential LRAC&ndash;market structure link. Electricity generation, water supply, and rail infrastructure all have very large MES relative to local demand &mdash; they naturally trend toward monopoly or near-monopoly. Restaurants, hairdressers, and local tradespeople have very small MES and support competitive, fragmented markets. This explains why Ofwat, Ofgem, and the ORR (Office of Rail and Road) regulate privatised utilities: breaking them into many small firms would push each above MES and <em>raise</em> costs, harming consumers.'
