    exp:'Economic profit = (&pound;3.80 &minus; &pound;3.80) &times; 300 = <strong>&pound;0</strong>: only normal profit in LR equilibrium. Excess capacity = 450 &minus; 300 = <strong>150 cups per day</strong>: the firm could reduce ATC by &pound;0.60 per cup if it expanded to 450, but demand is too limited. This is the Chamberlin excess capacity result: MC produces variety at the cost of productive inefficiency.'
