    exp:'<strong>Market stalls</strong> (most contestable): daily rental, zero dedicated capital, instant entry and exit. <strong>Coach routes</strong>: coaches are mobile and redeployable; Baumol cited inter-city bus routes as nearly perfectly contestable. <strong>Aviation</strong>: aircraft can be leased and redeployed, but airport slots, regulatory approval, and brand investment create meaningful sunk costs. <strong>Fixed-line broadband</strong> (least contestable): underground cable is wholly irrecoverable &mdash; a classic natural monopoly with near-total sunk costs. The ranking reflects the critical variable: how much of entry investment is recoverable on exit?'
