    exp:'(1) <strong>Free (costless)</strong>: no entry or exit barriers. (2) <strong>Sunk</strong>: costs that are irrecoverable on exit are the critical deterrent to entry; zero sunk costs means "hit and run" is costless. (3) <strong>Monopolist</strong>: Baumol\'s key point &mdash; even a single-firm market can be competitive in outcome if contestable. (4) <strong>Average total</strong>: P = ATC (normal profit) deprives entrants of profit; P = ATC is the limit price in a perfectly contestable market. (5) <strong>Hit-and-run</strong>: the entry strategy that contestability makes credible &mdash; enter, undercut, earn profit, exit before incumbent responds. (6) <strong>Sunk</strong>: the exit penalty; zero sunk costs = perfectly contestable; high sunk costs = weak contestability.'
