    exp:'(1) <strong>Vertical</strong>: in the Classical model, long-run output is fixed at Yfe by supply-side factors. (2) <strong>Price level</strong>: at Yfe, any AD increase is purely inflationary. (3) <strong>Horizontal</strong>: in the Keynesian model, at low output, firms can expand production by hiring idle resources without raising prices. (4) <strong>Spare capacity</strong>: unemployed workers, idle factories, unused land. (5) A <strong>negative</strong> output gap means actual output &lt; potential output. (6) <strong>Cyclical</strong> unemployment: the type that exists when the economy is below capacity &mdash; it disappears at Yfe. (7) <strong>Right</strong>: a rightward LRAS shift increases the economy&apos;s maximum sustainable output.'
